docs.abstract: Lukas Natkevicius’s personal story offers a counterpoint to critics who say people in the diversity visa program do not deserve the chance.
docs.snippet: Lukas Natkevicius’s personal story offers a counterpoint to critics who say people in the diversity visa program do not deserve the chance.
docs.lead_paragraph: KAZLU RUDA TRAINING AREA, Lithuania — A decade ago, Lukas Natkevicius and his family here in Lithuania won the lottery. Now he is back in this tiny Baltic nation — as a United States Army soldier helping to defend his former homeland.

headline.main: A Visa Lottery Winner a Decade Ago, a U.S. Soldier Returns Home to Lithuania
headline.print_headline: A lottery winner a decade ago, an Army soldier returns home to Lithuania

docs.abstract: A federal judge in Maryland seemed sympathetic to the plaintiff’s arguments that the president may be violating the Constitution.
docs.snippet: A federal judge in Maryland seemed sympathetic to the plaintiff’s arguments that the president may be violating the Constitution.
docs.lead_paragraph: GREENBELT, Md. — A federal judge on Monday sharply criticized the Justice Department’s argument that President Trump’s financial interest in his company’s hotel in downtown Washington is constitutional, a fresh sign that the judge may soon rule against the president in a historic case that could head to the Supreme Court.

headline.main: Judge in Emoluments Case Questions Defense of Trump’s Hotel Profits
headline.print_headline: Judge Questions Defense of President’s Hotel Profits

docs.abstract: A rebellion from conservative lawmakers sank a vast farm-policy bill on the House floor Friday amid a fight over how to proceed on immigration.
docs.snippet: A rebellion from conservative lawmakers sank a vast farm-policy bill on the House floor Friday amid a fight over how to proceed on immigration.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The factional rancor threatening Republicans heading into the midterm elections this fall erupted into the open on Friday when a slugfest among moderates, hard-line conservatives and House leaders over immigration and welfare policy sank the party’s multiyear farm bill.

headline.main: House Farm Bill Collapses Amid Republican Disarray
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Faction Sinks Vast Bill On Farm Policy

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump hit back on Friday at criticism over his administration’s hard-line stance on immigration, lamenting the “death and destruction caused by people that shouldn’t be here,” and accusing Democrats and the news media of not caring.

headline.main: Trump Highlights Immigrant Crime to Defend His Border Policy. Statistics Don’t Back Him Up.

docs.abstract: Hundreds of school districts across the country have given staff access to guns, seeing the weaponry not as a political statement but a practical response to a potent threat.
docs.snippet: Hundreds of school districts across the country have given staff access to guns, seeing the weaponry not as a political statement but a practical response to a potent threat.
docs.lead_paragraph: SIDNEY, Ohio — The 8-by-11-inch box sits atop a bookshelf in the district headquarters, as much a part of the office furniture as the manila folders, yearbooks and Webster’s dictionaries. Inside is a semiautomatic Glock handgun with extra magazines, equipment that education leaders here say will prevent this district from suffering the next schoolhouse tragedy.

headline.main: Trump Wants to Arm Teachers. These Schools Already Do.
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Call to Arm Teachers Resonates at Schools That Do

docs.abstract: The Treasury secretary was hissed at and cursed at during a lecture and discussion on the campus, and his shielding of the video has drawn more attention to the series of tense exchanges.
docs.snippet: The Treasury secretary was hissed at and cursed at during a lecture and discussion on the campus, and his shielding of the video has drawn more attention to the series of tense exchanges.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin was taunted with hisses, heckles and profanity during a lecture and moderated discussion at U.C.L.A. this week. Protesters were carried out by armed police officers. A sixth grader in the audience questioned him about the fairness of passing permanent tax cuts for companies and expiring cuts for individuals.

headline.main: Mnuchin Blocks U.C.L.A. From Releasing Video of Students Heckling Him
headline.print_headline: Mnuchin Blocks Release Of Student Heckling Video

docs.abstract: The justices have agreed to decide whether Vernon Madison, a 67-year-old who has suffered at least two severe strokes, can be executed for a killing he cannot recall.
docs.snippet: The justices have agreed to decide whether Vernon Madison, a 67-year-old who has suffered at least two severe strokes, can be executed for a killing he cannot recall.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The nation’s death rows are starting to look like geriatric wards. Condemned inmates in many states are more likely to die of natural causes than to be executed. The rare ones who are put to death often first spend decades behind bars, waiting.

headline.main: Too Old to Be Executed? Supreme Court Considers an Aging Death Row
headline.print_headline: Too Old to Be Executed? Justices Consider an Aging Death Row

docs.abstract: The lawyer admitted lying in an interview with the special counsel about conversations he had with Rick Gates, who served on the Trump campaign.
docs.snippet: The lawyer admitted lying in an interview with the special counsel about conversations he had with Rick Gates, who served on the Trump campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The son-in-law of a Russia-based billionaire admitted on Tuesday to lying to investigators about his communications with a former Trump campaign aide. The guilty plea by the defendant, a former lawyer at a powerful New York-based law firm, broadened the scope of the special counsel’s inquiry into Russia’s election interference.

headline.main: Former Skadden Lawyer Pleads Guilty to Lying in Russia Investigation
headline.print_headline: Guilty Plea by Lawyer Broadens Mueller Inquiry
